{"itemid":909,"subject":"Learn to Rite Good","event":"The Clarion West writer's workshop in Seattle has announced its lineup of instructors for 2012.\r\n\r\nI'm one of them.\r\n\r\nHere's the scoop:\r\n\r\nhttp://www.clarionwest.org/\r\n\r\nThe Clarion workshops are a sort of writer's boot camp.  They're not for everyone -- the criticism can be intense -- but for those who are willing to live, eat, drink, and breathe SF and fantasy for a summer, there's no better training.  Admission is pretty competitive as well.  Many apply, few are chosen.\r\n\r\nBut over the decades Clarion and Clarion West have turned out more professional SF and fantasy writers than all the college creative writing programs in the country combined.\r\n\r\nScholarships are available for those who cannot afford the tuition.","ditemid":232737,"eventtime":"2011-08-08 08:41:00","props":{"taglist":"appearances, writing, teaching","current_moodid":91,"commentalter":1313168700,"give_features":1,"picture_keyword":"Morocco","opt_screening":"F","personifi_tags":"nterms:yes","interface":"web"},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2011-08-08 14:41:21","anum":33,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html","event_timestamp":1312792860,"reply_count":15,"comments":[{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/38166420/1322587","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?replyto=14458657","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458657#t14458657","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458657#t14458657","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458657#t14458657","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"doesi","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://doesi.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":14458657,"talkid":56479,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458657#t14458657","upictitle":"Ford &quot;Rommel-I-Read-Your-Book&quot; Pendleton: [EMOFACE SHOCKED]","article":"The boldest statement I'll ever make:<br /><br />I'll see you there. Or I'll die trying.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"5 years ago","ctime":"August 8 2011, 17:16:35 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://doesi.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"doesi","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"doesi","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://doesi.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"doesi","ctime_ts":1312823795,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/108237744/2543627","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?replyto=14458913","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458913#t14458913","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458913#t14458913","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458913#t14458913","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"templarwolf","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://templarwolf.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":14458913,"talkid":56480,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14458913#t14458913","upictitle":"templarwolf: snake","article":"I'm curious to go to Clarion.  Odyssey was amazing.<br /><br />The problem I've seen with most college writing courses is how hostile the professors can be to genre fiction.  It largely seems if you write something other than the touchy-feely stuff you'd find promoted by Oprah, they want nothing to do with you.  Sometimes, the students are just as bad, though I've experienced that far more with MFA grad students than those in either the basic or advanced non-grad fiction classes.<br /><br />I once was called in to meet with an instructor because other students had complained I was \"attacking\" their work.  I critiqued their stories as I would a piece at Odyssey.  When I explained my background and why I was handling stories in such a manner (such as commenting that on page 14 of 16, something should have happened by now, and while the atmosphere was good, there was no tension), she responded that we shouldn't even be thinking of publication yet.  This is as a graduate level course...","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"5 years ago","ctime":"August 8 2011, 18:20:05 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://templarwolf.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"templarwolf","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"templarwolf","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://templarwolf.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"templarwolf","ctime_ts":1312827605,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/41206568/7235368","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?replyto=14459937","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459937#t14459937","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459937#t14459937","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459937#t14459937","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"barbarienne","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://barbarienne.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":14459937,"talkid":56484,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459937#t14459937","above":14458913,"upictitle":"barbarienne: pillage art","article":"I feel a need to defend at least some college-level writing courses. I hear so many horror stories similar to yours, that I must have had some exceptional good luck.<br /><br />I had two professors ban genre writing, but for a very sensible reason. Both noted that genre-specific writing has specialized issues for each genre, and they were teaching a general fiction-writing course. Neither got up my nose about my straightforward, nonpoetical style, and both were glad to have students who weren't afraid to critique firmly. Both encouraged me to keep writing after the semester ended.<br /><br />Obviously college writing courses aren't required--many of us start a hell of a lot younger than college or even high school--but if you're a college student and can get a course credit and fulfill a requirement by taking a class to do something you were going to do anyway... Research the profs first and see if the class is of the wifty sort or of the \"this is what published writers do\" variety.<br /><br />NB: My classes were at Queens College, part of the City University of New York. The proximity of the large commercial publishers may effect the approach they take.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"5 years ago","ctime":"August 8 2011, 20:34:31 UTC","parent":14458913,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://barbarienne.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"barbarienne","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"barbarienne","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://barbarienne.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"barbarienne","ctime_ts":1312835671,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/108237744/2543627","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?replyto=14460193","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14460193#t14460193","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14460193#t14460193","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14460193#t14460193","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"templarwolf","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://templarwolf.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":14460193,"talkid":56485,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14460193#t14460193","above":14459937,"upictitle":"templarwolf: snake","article":"True, not all college writing courses are the same.  My grad-course experience is probably also colored by the fact that the instructor is a \"chick-lit\" author, and the only woman among the students seemed bound and determined to act the part of the stereotypical angry lesbian.  It also turned out the instructor was one of the candidates for a professorship here, and the word from those in the know is she would've been turned down, even if the other 15 applicants had declined the offer.<br /><br />The two professor you had sounds like true professionals.  Their reasons are sound and I can respect them for it.<br /><br />On the other hand, I had one professor, in particular, who not only allowed genre fiction, she gave very good feedback on it.  She did have some rules, such as \"No zombie stories\" based on previous experiences in class.  However, she was also willing to work with us.  I asked her permission to break the zombie rule, as I wanted a piece critiqued I was writing with a specific anthology in mind.  It also ran longer than her usual limit.  She allowed it, and that story went on to become my first publishing credit.<br /><br />Because of her, I'm now looking to get into the MFA program here.  I work for the university and get to take classes for free, I may as well get an advanced degree...","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"5 years ago","ctime":"August 8 2011, 20:49:27 UTC","parent":14459937,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://templarwolf.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"templarwolf","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"templarwolf","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://templarwolf.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"templarwolf","ctime_ts":1312836567,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/107736900/193563","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?replyto=14459169","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459169#t14459169","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459169#t14459169","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459169#t14459169","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"syrensix","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://syrensix.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":14459169,"talkid":56481,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/232737.html?thread=14459169#t14459169","upictitle":"Sparro